darthgrim



Cedar Park, Texas





Level 6  Contributor 


184 reviews 


43 restaurant reviews





76 helpful votes 





“Good beer with lots of community style seating”


Reviewed 3 weeks ago




Beers can be purchased individually or by the flight. They have two preset flights (their signature series or year round beers, and the ex-girlfriend flight of their fruited beers - Feisty Blonde, Feisty Brunette, Feisty Redhead, and Thorny Blonde) or you can do a custom one. In addition to their core four brews you are rewarded with many taproom only selections. I especially liked their Feisty Redhead, a cherry/hibiscus ale, and their Zombie Crack, a pecan bourbon barrel stout. Fruit beers and stouts seemed to be their main focus on my visit, and I only saw one IPA on tap.There was lots of community style seating available, inside and outside on their deck. People had brought small children and there were board games available. Several people had also brought dogs and I even saw one in the taproom.








 



 


  



Visited July 2017



Value





Service






Helpful? 


Thank darthgrim 





Report 




Ask darthgrim about HopFusion Ale Works



